              "type": "Annotation",
              "motivation": "commenting",
              "body": [
                {
                  "type": "TextualBody",
                  "value": "<p>Latin inscriptions appear on many pages in Joris Hoefnagel’s albums, including this one.&nbsp;</p>",
                  "language": "en",
                  "format": "text/html"
                }
              ],
              "target": "https://ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com/node/919636/canvases/1#xywh=0,0,5588,4453"
            },
            {
              "id": "https://ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com/node/919636/pages/text/1/annotation/1",
              "type": "Annotation",
              "motivation": "commenting",
              "body": [
                {
                  "type": "TextualBody",
                  "value": "<p>These inscriptions are bits of poetry, mottos, or proverbs that impart a moral or lesson.</p>",
                  "language": "en",
                  "format": "text/html",
                  "position-hint": "south"
                }
              ],
              "target": "https://ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com/node/919636/canvases/1#xywh=800,22,3817,726"
            },
            {
              "id": "https://ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com/node/919636/pages/text/1/annotation/2",
              "type": "Annotation",
              "motivation": "commenting",
              "body": [
                {
                  "type": "TextualBody",
                  "value": "<p>Texts at the top and bottom compare a hedgehog with a fox. The bottom inscription reads “The fox has many tricks, but the hedgehog has one great trick.”&nbsp;</p>",
                  "language": "en",
                  "format": "text/html",
                  "position-hint": "north"
                }
              ],
              "target": "https://ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com/node/919636/canvases/1#xywh=813,3708,3536,726"
            },
            {
              "id": "https://ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com/node/919636/pages/text/1/annotation/3",
              "type": "Annotation",
              "motivation": "commenting",
              "body": [
                {
                  "type": "TextualBody",
                  "value": "<p>Its trick? Rolling into a ball when it feels threatened.&nbsp;</p>",
                  "language": "en",
                  "format": "text/html",
                  "position-hint": "north"
                },
                {
                  "type": "Image",
                  "NOT-id": "/sites/default/files/2025-02/comphedgehog.jpg",
                  "id": "https://benr-cogapp.github.io/benr-cogapp/tempiiies/NGA/compHedgehog744.jpg",
                  "format": "image/jpeg"
                }
              ],
              "target": "https://ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com/node/919636/canvases/1#xywh=813,3708,3536,726"
            },
            {
              "id": "https://ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com/node/919636/pages/text/1/annotation/4",
              "type": "Annotation",
              "motivation": "commenting",
              "body": [
                {
                  "type": "TextualBody",
                  "value": "<p>Its trick? Rolling into a ball when it feels threatened.&nbsp;</p>",
                  "language": "en",
                  "format": "text/html",
                  "position-hint": "west"
                }
              ],
              "target": "https://ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com/node/919636/canvases/1#xywh=3370,2065,1326,859"
            },
            {
              "id": "https://ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com/node/919636/pages/text/1/annotation/5",
              "type": "Annotation",
              "motivation": "commenting",
              "body": [
                {
                  "type": "TextualBody",
                  "value": "<p>The &nbsp;plaque above the rolled hedgehog reads “No strength is anything but an error.” Hoefnagel suggests that the hedgehog’s seemingly weak defense mechanism should be admired.</p>",
                  "language": "en",
                  "format": "text/html",
                  "position-hint": "west"
                }
              ],
              "target": "https://ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com/node/919636/canvases/1#xywh=3321,849,1209,1146"
            },
            {
              "id": "https://ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com/node/919636/pages/text/1/annotation/6",
              "type": "Annotation",
              "motivation": "commenting",
              "body": [
                {
                  "type": "TextualBody",
                  "value": "<p>One more inscription is hidden, written in gold below the central hedgehog. It reads: “I wrap myself in virtue.”</p>",
                  "language": "en",
                  "format": "text/html",
                  "position-hint": "south"
                }
              ],
              "target": "https://ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com/node/919636/canvases/1#xywh=1880,1760,1607,955"
            },
            {
              "id": "https://ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com/node/919636/pages/text/1/annotation/7",
              "type": "Annotation",
              "motivation": "commenting",
              "body": [
                {
                  "type": "TextualBody",
                  "value": "<p>What lesson does the hedgehog offer us?</p>",
                  "language": "en",
                  "format": "text/html"
                }
              ],
              "target": "https://ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com/node/919636/canvases/1#xywh=0,0,5588,4453"
            },
            {
              "id": "https://ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com/node/919636/pages/text/1/annotation/8",
              "type": "Annotation",
              "motivation": "commenting",
              "body": [
                {
                  "type": "TextualBody",
                  "value": "<p>One scholar proposed that Hoefnagel wants us to applaud the hedgehog’s self-defense tactic—that its “one great trick” can be useful, even virtuous, when faced with aggression.</p>",
                  "language": "en",
                  "format": "text/html",
                  "position-hint": "north"
                }
              ],
              "target": "https://ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com/node/919636/canvases/1#xywh=1880,1760,2838,1179"
            },
            {
              "id": "https://ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com/node/919636/pages/text/1/annotation/9",
              "type": "Annotation",
              "motivation": "commenting",
              "body": [
                {
                  "type": "TextualBody",
                  "value": "<p>Do you agree with this? What’s YOUR one great trick?</p>",
                  "language": "en",
                  "format": "text/html"
                }
              ],
              "target": "https://ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com/node/919636/canvases/1#xywh=0,0,5588,4453"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
